"Sommer R.S., Fritz U., Seppä H., Ekström J., Persson A., Liljegren R.","When the pond turtle followed the reindeer: Effect of the last extreme global warming event on the timing of faunal change in Northern Europe",2011,"Global Change Biology","17","6",,"2049","2053",,,10.1111/j.1365-2486.2011.02388.x,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-79954993388&partnerID=40&md5=b20a3a1f591e4a0a55c9881c1c74b81a","Ecology Centre, University of Kiel, Olshausenstraße 40, D-24098 Kiel, Germany; Museum of Zoology, Senckenberg Dresden, A. B. Meyer Building, D-01109 Dresden, Germany; Department of Geosciences and Geography, University of Helsinki, Helsinki FI-00014, Finland; Museum of Zoology, Lund University, Helgonavägen 3, S-223 62 Lund, Sweden; Department of Earth and Ecosystem Sciences, Lund University, Sölvegatan 12, S-223 62 Lund, Sweden","Sommer, R.S., Ecology Centre, University of Kiel, Olshausenstraße 40, D-24098 Kiel, Germany; Fritz, U., Museum of Zoology, Senckenberg Dresden, A. B. Meyer Building, D-01109 Dresden, Germany; Seppä, H., Department of Geosciences and Geography, University of Helsinki, Helsinki FI-00014, Finland; Ekström, J., Museum of Zoology, Lund University, Helgonavägen 3, S-223 62 Lund, Sweden; Persson, A., Department of Earth and Ecosystem Sciences, Lund University, Sölvegatan 12, S-223 62 Lund, Sweden; Liljegren, R., Museum of Zoology, Lund University, Helgonavägen 3, S-223 62 Lund, Sweden, Department of Earth and Ecosystem Sciences, Lund University, Sölvegatan 12, S-223 62 Lund, Sweden","Faunal communities have been shaped in different ways by past climatic change. The impact of the termination of the last Glacial and the onset of the present (Holocene) Interglacial on large-scale faunal shifts, extinction dynamics and gene pools of species are of special interest in natural sciences. A general pattern of climate-triggered range expansion and local extinction of vertebrate species is known for Europe, and shows that in the modern temperate zone the main faunal change took place mainly during the Late Glacial (14700-11700 years ago) and Early Holocene (11700-9100 years ago). Based on large datasets of new radiocarbon data, we present precise temporal dynamics of climate-driven disappearance and appearance of reindeer and pond turtle in southern Sweden. These two species are significant climate indicators in Late Quaternary biostratigraphy. Our data reveal that the reindeer disappeared from southern Sweden ca. 10300 years ago, whereas the pond turtle colonized the area ca. 9860 years ago, with a 450-year gap between each species. This provides evidence for a sudden environmental turnover, causing the replacement of an arctic faunal element by a thermophilic species. The postglacial range dynamics of pond turtle and reindeer are a unique model case, allowing insights into the faunal turnover of other vertebrates during the last dramatic natural global warming event at the Pleistocene-Holocene transition. © 2011 Blackwell Publishing Ltd.","Emys orbicularis; Extinction; Holocene; Late Glacial; Quaternary; Range shift; Rangifer tarandus; Sweden","biostratigraphy; deer; extinction; extreme event; global warming; Holocene; Last Glacial; range expansion; turtle; Sweden; Emydidae; Emys orbicularis; Rangifer tarandus; Testudines; Vertebrata",,,,,,"Aaris-Sørensen, K., Muhldorff, R., Petersen, E.B., The Scandinavian reindeer (Rangifer tarandus L.) after the last glacial maximum (2007) Journal of Archaeological Science, 34, pp. 914-923. , time, seasonality and human exploitation; Berglund, B.E., Björck, S., Lemdahl, G., Late Weichselian environmental change in southern Sweden and Denmark (1994) Journal of Quaternary Science, 9, pp. 127-132; Björck, S., A review of the history of the Baltic Sea, 13.0-8.0ka BP (1995) Quaternary International, 27, pp. 19-40; Björck, S., The late Quaternary development of the Baltic Sea basin (2008) Assessment of climate change for the Baltic Sea Basin, pp. 398-407. , In: (eds The BACC Author Team) - Springer, Berlin; Björck, S., Walker, M.J.C., Cwynar, L.C., An event stratigraphy for the Last Termination in the North Atlantic region based on the Greenland ice-core record (1998) Journal of Quaternary Science, 13, pp. 283-292. , a proposal by the INTIMATE group; Dansgaard, W., Johnsen, S.J., Clausen, H.B., Evidence for general instability of past climate from a 250-kyr ice-core record (1993) Nature, 364, pp. 218-220; Fritz, U., Emys orbicularis (Linnaeus, 1758) - Europäische Sumpfschildkröte (2001) Handbuch der Reptilien und Amphibien Europas Vol. 3/IIIa: Schildkröten (Testudines) I, pp. 343-523. , In: (ed Fritz U) - Aula, Wiebelsheim; Herre, W., Rangifer tarandus (Linnaeus, 1758) - Rentier (1986) Handbuch der Säugetiere Europas Vol. 2/II Paarhufer, pp. 198-216. , In: (eds Niethammer J, Krapp F) - Aula, Wiesbaden; Hewitt, G., The genetic legacy of the Quaternary ice ages (2000) Nature, 405, pp. 907-913; Hofreiter, M., Stewart, J.R., Ecological change, range fluctuations and review population dynamics during the Pleistocene (2009) Current Biology, 19, pp. 584-594; Huntley, B., Alfano, M.J., Allen, J.R.M., European vegetation during Marine Oxygen Isotope Stage-3 (2003) Quaternary Research, 59, pp. 159-212; Semken, H.A., Graham, R.W., Stafford, T.W., AMS 14C analysis of Late Pleistocene non-analog faunal components from 21 cave deposits in southeastern North America (2010) Quaternary International, 217, pp. 240-255; Sommer, R.S., Benecke, N., Late- and Post-Glacial history of the Mustelidae in Europe (2004) Mammal Review, 34, pp. 249-284; Sommer, R.S., Benecke, N., Late-Pleistocene and early Holocene history of the canid fauna of Europe (Canidae) (2005) Mammalian Biology, 70, pp. 227-241; Sommer, R.S., Lindqvist, C., Persson, A., Unexpected early extinction of the European pond turtle (Emys orbicularis) in Sweden and climatic impact on its Holocene range (2009) Molecular Ecology, 18, pp. 1252-1262; Sommer, R.S., Persson, A., Wiesecke, N., Fritz, U.